title: Sidewall, ca. 1875
inscribed: Paper 1939-45-11 used as frieze with this. See advertisement of James Toleman, Paper-Hanging Manufacturers, London. in Furniture Gazette, London, June 2, 1877, p. XVI
creditline: Gift of Edith and Maude Wetmore
description: Full width, giving slightly more than one repeat of slender vine pattern of conventionalized passion-flowers (roses), against secondary all-over pattern of foliation. Paper embossed with a pebbled figure. Printed in blue, green and tans, on grey-violet ground.

tombstone.epitaph:
Sidewall, ca. 1875.
ca. 1875. Machine-printed, embossed paper. Gift of Edith and Maude Wetmore. 1939-45-7-a,b.
